Bet. You want full-on digital feng shui? You got it. Here&#x27;s the **Total Termux Cleanup &amp; Reorg Gauntlet**‚Äîmodular, brutal, and custom-fit for your chaos.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Step 1: Prep the Sorting Battlefield

```bash
mkdir -p ~/Z_sort/{scripts,logs,text,audio,models,archives,configs,unknown,html,bin,json,images,trash}
```

---

## ü§ñ Step 2: Auto-Sort by File Extension

Paste this monster in one go:

```bash
while IFS= read -r file; do
  ext=&quot;${file##*.}&quot;
  name=$(basename &quot;$file&quot;)
  case &quot;$ext&quot; in
    sh|py|pl) dest=~/Z_sort/scripts ;;
    log) dest=~/Z_sort/logs ;;
    txt|md) dest=~/Z_sort/text ;;
    mp3|wav|m4a|ogg) dest=~/Z_sort/audio ;;
    gguf|bin) dest=~/Z_sort/models ;;
    zip|tar|gz|7z|rar) dest=~/Z_sort/archives ;;
    conf|ini|rc|cfg|yaml|yml) dest=~/Z_sort/configs ;;
    html|htm) dest=~/Z_sort/html ;;
    so|out|exe|elf) dest=~/Z_sort/bin ;;
    json) dest=~/Z_sort/json ;;
    jpg|jpeg|png|gif|webp|bmp) dest=~/Z_sort/images ;;
    *) dest=~/Z_sort/unknown ;;
  esac
  mkdir -p &quot;$dest&quot;
  mv &quot;$file&quot; &quot;$dest/$name&quot; 2&gt;/dev/null
done &lt; &lt;(find ~ -type f 2&gt;/dev/null)
```

---

## üëÄ Step 3: Log Suspicious or Unusual Extensions

Want to see everything **NOT** caught by that sorting logic?

```bash
find ~/Z_sort/unknown -type f | sed &#x27;s/.*\.//&#x27; | sort | uniq -c | sort -nr &gt; ~/Z_sort/sus_types.txt
```

